{"id":14880937,"mediaExerciseId":"02904116-d95f-4d4d-81f0-c6cbdf2c882e","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612300,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":183,"solutions":[{"id":5960624,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will determine the impact of increasing or decreasing the rate in perpetuity.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/0a65ecc5bbbe918c2fb90081edf92cde/d2ab0d931bf447558e2e19b3e9305b79/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/0a65ecc5bbbe918c2fb90081edf92cde/d2ab0d931bf447558e2e19b3e9305b79/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Perpetuity** or otherwise known as *consols* refers to a constant annuity without a maturity date.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/0a65ecc5bbbe918c2fb90081edf92cde/3517b306127494099274d9b1c63340ee/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/0a65ecc5bbbe918c2fb90081edf92cde/3517b306127494099274d9b1c63340ee/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Since perpetuity has no end and has an infinite number of cash flows, an increase or decrease in the interest rate will have no effect. There is no point in calculating the future value of constant cash flows with an infinite period; hence, perpetuity's future value will remain undefined.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/0a65ecc5bbbe918c2fb90081edf92cde/9437d848009cdb584aafb032d2eb82c2/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/0a65ecc5bbbe918c2fb90081edf92cde/9437d848009cdb584aafb032d2eb82c2/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"7e49453a-a04f-4a6a-b2bb-8b22ab519eba","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3},{"id":6359320,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We need to determine the change in perpetuity when interest rate increases.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Perpetuity is simply **eternal annuity**, ie. constant deposit occurring in constant periods which happens forever.\n\n**Present value of perpetuity** is defined as:\n\n$$\\text{PV}=\\frac{\\text{C}}{\\text{r}}$$\n\nwhere:\n\n$\\text{C}$ = deposit amount;\\\n$\\text{r}$ = interest rate.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"As we can see, present value of perpetuity is **inversely proportional to the value of interest rate**, ie. as $\\text{r}$ increases, $\\text{PV}$ decreases.\n\nTherefore **perpetuity value decreases with increase in interest rate**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"02d707e5-c669-45f2-aa0b-221c36493e36","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880938,"exerciseName":"12","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"650d142c-346b-4af4-bc69-368dffd41b30","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-12-650d142c-346b-4af4-bc69-368dffd41b30"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880936,"exerciseName":"10","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"06e014cf-0c75-41be-a892-f6da400c84f5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-10-06e014cf-0c75-41be-a892-f6da400c84f5"},{"id":14880935,"exerciseName":"9","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a8c6df91-a8d4-416e-91a2-068202b1e967","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-9-a8c6df91-a8d4-416e-91a2-068202b1e967"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-11-02904116-d95f-4d4d-81f0-c6cbdf2c882e"}